fields.summary: Multiple launch configurations causes session to timeout

comments.body: Changed this to blocker because the issue is actually happening when more than one launch configuration(s) exist.  I get the same error as described in the description.  I also changed the summary to reflect the behavior.

reproduced issue on 7/2 during sprint demo. Console said 2015-07-02 13:29:25,265 INFO  [root][Dummy-2] ui-test-acct-00/admin@127.0.0.1 [DcYYcBDHzhyaVNHP]: Creating launch configuration demoLC2
2015-07-02 13:29:28,085 ERROR [root][Dummy-4] ui-test-acct-00/admin@127.0.0.1 [dpV92I5jIvTUt0je]: The image 'emi-87c97f2a' does not exist
2015-07-02 13:29:36,478 INFO  [root][Dummy-4] Authenticated Eucalyptus user: ui-test-acct-00/admin from 127.0.0.1
2015-07-02 13:29:48,110 ERROR [root][Dummy-3] ui-test-acct-00/admin@127.0.0.1 [lbc9dspORDGYQaBT]: The image 'emi-87c97f2a' does not exist
2015-07-02 13:29:55,921 INFO  [root][Dummy-4] Authenticated Eucalyptus user: ui-test-acct-00/admin from 127.0.0.1
2015-07-02 13:32:58,114 INFO  [root][Dummy-4] ui-test-acct-00/admin@127.0.0.1 [A4OMiCb7m3c2WX5W]: Creating elastic load balancer demo-ELB
2015-07-02 13:38:04,770 ERROR [root][Dummy-2] ui-test-acct-00/admin@127.0.0.1 [2U1TltLB8nywriVh]: The image 'emi-87c97f2a' does not exist

But the image is there.

It looks like this is an odd little bug in the CLC which I can easily work around. Unsure what the CLC should do, but an error is probably not the best result. [~sjones], mind commenting?
I found that in this case, both launch configs have the same image. So we run a DescribeImages fetch with a filter which specifies the same image id twice. I'll change that so that the list is full of unique ids, but I wonder what the CLC should do in this case? It does complain that the image doesn't exist.

[~dkavanagh], I think you are referring to this issue, which is fixed in 4.2 - EUCA-10874. Filtering will select specific items from the response, if the item would not be in the response, it will not be added due to a filter. With images for example you may need to specify other options to ensure that visible images from other accounts would be included.

[~sjones], In this case, the image is definitely visible to this account. If I specify that image once in the filter, the image record is returned. When I specify the id twice in the filter, that's when this error occurs. I assume it's an odd error due to the image being requested already being in the result set, but I haven't looked at the filter code to see.
[~dkavanagh], if the issue occurs with the current code from master then please open a bug for it, but I expect it was fixed with EUCA-10874.
[~dkavanagh], there is still a problem with incorrect NotFound errors, but not when using filters. I've opened EUCA-11068 with the details.

Our setup : http://10.111.4.1/job/Quick%20Launch%20Master/355/
was built on June 15th. I saw your commit was June 10th, but not sure if that was on your feature branch or merged to master.
Dang, I'm sorry. I looked at our code again and we're not using filters. It's the problem you filed in EUCA-11068. exactly.

Verified.  I was able to create 3 launch configurations and did not get logged out.
